documents.title: Python Setup Guide
documents.content: To set up Python on your system, download the latest version from python.org. Follow the installation wizard and ensure to add Python to PATH during installation. Verify installation with 'python --version'.

documents.title: Common API Errors
documents.content: 401 Unauthorized: Invalid API key. Check your credentials in .env file. 429 Too Many Requests: Rate limit exceeded. Wait before retrying. 500 Internal Server Error: Server issue, try again later.

documents.title: Security Best Practices
documents.content: Never commit API keys to version control. Use .env files and add them to .gitignore. Rotate keys regularly. Use environment variables for sensitive data. Enable two-factor authentication on all accounts.

documents.title: Database Connection FAQ
documents.content: Q: How do I connect to PostgreSQL? A: Use psycopg2 library: import psycopg2; conn = psycopg2.connect(). Q: How to handle connection pooling? A: Use pgBouncer or sqlalchemy connection pools.
